Aug 15 2009	It was great!	Must say that me and my friend were a little intimidated by all the reviews, we had booked before we read any of them. And good thing we didn't read! I can't believe so many have had such bad experiences, because we faced hardly any problems during our stay.Okay true that it could use a minor update (especially the carpets) but we didn't mind that at all.As we were checking in we encountered one of the most helpful and nice receptionists ever (long brown hair, piercing in nose, very smiley) who provided us with lots of info and tips throughout our stay. As we headed up to our room we noticed that one of the two elevators was broken, but it had been fixed already the same night. So no problems there.Our room was situated on the 2nd floor, the window facing Cromwell Road, which is a very busy street even in nighttime. Once closed, the window blocked out surprisingly much of the noise, but I'd still recommend to bring a pair of earplugs. Pop them in your ears and you'll sleep like a baby through the remaining traffic sounds.The room itself was very basic, but provided us with all that we needed; Two single beds (as we had requested) comfortable, neatly made, clean sheets &amp; fairly comfy pillows, enough table- and closet space and a clean bathroom. We both had large suitcases and placing them open on the floor called for a little puzzling, but we managed fine.As mentioned, our bathroom was great, nothing nasty bout it. Sink and tub were both clean, towels and soaps were changed every time, the shower worked just fine (not too cold or too hot) and had good waterpressure. Even our toilet was scrubbed every time!Now, you need to pay attetion when closing your door. Especially if you leave your window open, and try closing the door too hard, it'll just pop right open again. So close with care, and double check, and you'll be just fine. The key needs to be left at the reception, but you get this &quot;room ID-card&quot; that you'll need to show every time you retrieve your key.I can't comment neither the restaurant nor the breakfast, since we ate out every day.And I would have wished for the rooms to be equipped with a fridge and a safe, but again, that's just me. And you'll be fine off without them as well.For the location; it was fabulous! Close to two tube stations, museums, Harrods, Hyde Park, eating, pubs...you name it!And the big Sainsburys (open 24 hrs during weekdays) was a nice plus as well.So me and my friend absolutely recommend the Majestic to all those travelling on a budget and aren't too picky :)	
