Sep 1 2006 	Small not squeeky clean but basically had what I wanted.	First, you should know that I don't care much for luxuries, all I want is a clean room, a clean bed, and my own clean bathroom. As long as I have that, I'm happy. When I'm on vacation I don't plan on staying in my hotelroom a lot, except to get some sleep and take a nice hot shower. I stayed here during Easter Weekend with a friend of mine. I only looked for reviews AFTER I booked my stay on Hotels, not the smartest thing to do I know, but hey, it had been a while since I actually went traveling abroad. Anyway, after having read the reviews here on tripadvisor, I was feeling reluctant to stay at this hotel. But it would've cost me a penalty fee to cancel the reservation and we would only stay there for 2 nights, we figured we would go ahead and see what would happen.Upon arrival, the exterior gave me a slight sense of dread, seeing how the walls were stained and had small cracks here and there. Entering the lobby you felt the much talked about heat hitting you in the face, although it wasn't as bad as I thought it would've been, having read the reviews. Yes, you do tend to sweat because of the heat, but it doesn't feel like some sort of desert dry heat or something. Another thing that caught my attention is the way the lobby looked, which hadn't exactly aged with grace, but again, it wasn't enough to scare the heck out of me.After having left our luggage in a small, simple locked room (we couldn't check in yet, since we arrived 10 AM) we went to do some exploring in London and upon returning around 8 PM, we finally saw our room. And yes, it was quite small, large enough to place our small travelbags on the floor, leaving enough room to walk to the bathroom back and forth without stumbling over our things, but don't expect to place down large duffel bags or suitcases easily. There was a closet for us to hang some clothes in. It didn't look very sturdy, and it only had about 2 or 3 hangers in it, but this too was okay. The carpet was quite worn in certain places, the drapes were dusty and had dark stains and were even torn here and there. The beds were okay, large enough for a grown man (I'm about 1.78 metres or 5 feet and 10 inches I believe?), leaving about 25 cm/10 inch of space between the bed end and my feet.. I did feel the springs in my back, but not something that kept me from me sleeping. They also looked quite clean, no strange stains or hair from other guests were found for that matter *chuckle*. What did kept me from getting a good nights rest was the traffic outside, since the window only had a single pane of glass, traffic noise isn't kept out very well. And because it was so warm too in our room, my friend wanted to keep the window open...I could've lived with the heat, but the traffic is just a sleep killer and it doesn't really stop at all during the night.The bathroom was quite good actually, there was a shower/bath, a large counter to put our toiletries on with a decent sink. and a toilet that worked the way it should, no complaints really. Except that on the last night we didn't have any hot water anymore. Actually, I was still able to take a decent shower, but my friend had to try and shower with cold water. Yes, she cursed and scowled pretty much the rest of that evening at me.All in all, it didn't turn out into the weekend from Hell for me, as for my friend, well, she does care about certain things more than me. Anyway, like I said, I don't expect and need a lot from a hotelroom. As long it's clean, with a clean bed and has a private bathroom I'm happy. The &quot;clean room&quot; bit scores about 6 out of 10 as far as I'm concerned. The bed was good enough to sleep in, no bugs seen. And the bathroom except for the cold water was up to my expectations. My friend on the other hand complained pretty much about everything, the heat, the carpet, the drapes, the cold water, the &quot;hard&quot; beds the noise. If you're like me, you'll probably do fine here, except for during the summer, with the central heating and all. And you might want to ask for a room not looking out on the street because of the noise, but other then that, you should be fine. Want something better, well, the Marriot is just across the street, for 4-5 times the price we paid here.	
Mar 11 2006	One word: DISGUSTING	This is not a hotel. It is a pit.I booked 3-nights. Upon arrival I was shown the most miserable room I've ever come across. Dirty and stained. I couldn't even imagine sitting on the bed, let alone sleeping on it. There were 2 guys patching something when I opened the door. Just walking to the room, based on the hallway and lobby I knew it would be bad.I bailed to a i-inet cafe down the street and booked the Country Inn and Suites across the street, which was pleasant. Majestic took my money, no refund.I don't usually take time to write reviews, but I felt it necessary to warn people in this case. City officials should condemn this place.	
